          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A nickel-coated disk sample of 239Pu having",
                "dimensions of 0.5-in. diameter and 0.125-in. thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The los Alamos Water boiler provided a 2-in",
                "diameter thermal neutron beam. The C2 nuclear",
                "emulsions plates were placed at right angles to the",
                "beam at a distance of 20 cm from the plutonium",
                "sample. A 35-hr irradiation at a power of 5.5 kW gave",
                "suitable proton recoil track density in nuclear",
                "plates. The data were accumulated from a total of",
                "5500 proton recoil tracks."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The measured relative neutron intensity, N(E), was",
                "given as function of the neutron energy, E; the",
                "tracks per unit energy interval have been divided by",
                "the scattering cross section of hydrogen, sigma p,",
                "corrected for tracks leaving the emulsion surfaces.",
                "Unfortunately, this method does not allow to",
                "discriminate between prompt and delayed neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
